############################# Cassandra DB Notes ###################################

#### Concepts

# KeySpace : Contains one or more tables;defines options for * tables in it,eg replication;

# Tables : Logical entiity that organizes data at cluster and node level acc to given schema;data is stored in rows of columns;tables can be altered,dropped,created without impacting running queries;

# Table Schema : defines at least "primary key" and regular columns of table

# Primary Key : subset of columns of table;mandatory on create table;immutable;has 2 parts: "partition key" and >=1 "clustering keys"(optional)  

#### Installation


#### CQL (Cassandra Query Language;similar to SQL)

## is "CASE-INSENSITIVE";stores all table names in lower case

### Basics (all ends with ; , hail ;)

# show host : show details of server connected to
# show version : get version
# describe keyspaces : get list of key spaces
# CREATE KEYSPACE <key_space name> WITH <options> : create new key space
# CREATE TABLE <table_name> (<columns and keys>) : similar to SQL
# INSERT INTO <table name> values ()
# SELECt * FROM <table name> WHERE ...
# UPDATE <table name> SET <colunm = value> WHERE ...
# DELETE FROM <table> WHERE ...
# DROP TABLE <table>;
# TRUNCATE TABLE <table>;


### Special Commands
# CAPTURE : send output of command to a file
# CONSISTENCY : show consistency level and set new one
# COPY : copy data to and from cassandra
# DESCRIBE : describe current cluster
# EXIT : termin8 cqlsh session
# PAGING : enable/disable paging of queries
# TRACING : EN/DI request tracing


